Stock Trend Analyzer Project Report
1. Abstract

This project presents a Stock Trend Analyzer developed using Python to analyze and visualize stock price data. The system computes key statistical metrics such as average, maximum, and minimum prices, along with daily and percentage changes. It also visualizes stock trends using line plots and moving averages, enabling better understanding of stock behavior over time.

2. Introduction

Stock market analysis is essential for understanding price movements and making informed financial decisions. This project focuses on building a simple yet effective tool to analyze stock price trends using numerical and graphical techniques.

The analyzer processes stock data, performs statistical analysis, and generates visual insights such as trend lines and daily changes.

3. Objectives
To analyze stock price data using numerical methods
To calculate statistical measures (mean, max, min)
To determine daily and percentage changes
To visualize stock trends using graphs
To implement moving average analysis
4. Technologies Used
Programming Language: Python
Libraries:
NumPy (for numerical computations)
Matplotlib (for data visualization)
5. Methodology
Step 1: Data Collection

The program uses predefined sample stock price data:

[100, 102, 101, 105, 110, 108, 112, 115]
Step 2: Data Processing

The data is converted into a NumPy array for efficient computation.

Step 3: Statistical Analysis

The following metrics are calculated:

Average price using mean
Maximum price
Minimum price
Step 4: Trend Analysis
Daily price changes are calculated using difference between consecutive values
Percentage changes are computed to measure relative variation
Step 5: Visualization

Two types of graphs are generated:

Stock Price Trend Graph
Daily Changes Graph
6. System Architecture

Input Layer:

Predefined stock price dataset

Processing Layer:

NumPy-based computations
Trend analysis calculations

Output Layer:

Printed statistical summary
Graphical visualizations using Matplotlib
7. Implementation Details
7.1 Data Loading

The load_data() function returns sample stock prices as a NumPy array.

7.2 Analysis Function

The analyze() function performs:

Mean calculation
Maximum and minimum detection
Daily change computation using np.diff()
Percentage change calculation
7.3 Visualization Functions
Plot 1: Stock Prices
Displays price trend using a line graph
Includes markers for each data point
Calculates and plots moving average using convolution
Uses a default window size of 3 days
Plot 2: Daily Changes
Bar chart for daily price changes
Line plot for percentage changes
Combined visualization improves interpretation
7.4 Main Function
Calls all functions in sequence
Displays summary output
Shows graphs using plt.show()
8. Results

The program successfully:

Computes statistical metrics
Identifies price fluctuations
Displays trends visually
Highlights short-term trends using moving averages

The graphs provide clear insights into stock movement patterns.

9. Advantages
Simple and easy to understand
Efficient numerical computation using NumPy
Clear graphical representation
No external data dependency
10. Limitations
Uses static sample data (no real-time data)
Limited to basic analysis techniques
Small dataset size
No predictive modeling
